==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deserter
<hw>De*sert"er</hw> <fld>(d⟦esl⟧*z⟦etil⟧rt"⟦etil⟧r)</fld>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>One who forsakes a duty, a cause or a party, a friend, or any one
to whom he owes service; especially, a soldier or a seaman who abandons
the service without leave; one guilty of desertion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Desertful</ent>⟦br⟧
